The solution sorts both arrays `a` and `b` along the specified axis (in this case, axis 0). The `np.argsort()` function returns an array of indices that would sort `a`, and `np.take_along_axis()` uses these indices to rearrange both `a` and `b`. This results in `sorted_b` being sorted according to the values in `sorted_a`.
